The paper deals with multi-view learning, which is a subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). The approach presented in the paper is applied to both synthetic and audio-visual databases, which suggests that it could be relevant to computer vision (cs.CV) and multimedia (cs.MM) research. The paper also discusses the issue of view corruption and noise, which could be related to signal processing (cs.SD) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
